rTrapAddrTable.description: Table of managers to which traps must be sent. Up to 10 entries in table

rTrapAddrAddr.name: rTrapAddrAddr
rTrapAddrAddr.description: IP address of entity requesting event notification

rTrapAddrComm.name: rTrapAddrComm
rTrapAddrComm.description: Community name the receiving entity will expect. When reading the instance of this object the value has no meaning.

rTrapAddrVer.name: rTrapAddrVer
rTrapAddrVer.description: Version number supported by destination node

rTrapAddrType.name: rTrapAddrType
rTrapAddrType.description: Type of event that should be reported to this address, bit 0 - authentication trap bit 1 - other SNMP traps bit 2 - Error Traps bit 3 - Diagnostic Traps bit 4 - Debug Traps bit 5 - Enterprise Traps other than fmDiagGenericTrap

rTrapAddrFlag.name: rTrapAddrFlag
rTrapAddrFlag.description: If the entry is fixed, it can not be deleted because of aging

rTrapAddrAge.name: rTrapAddrAge
rTrapAddrAge.description: Aging time of the entry (in sec)

rTrapLearning.name: rTrapLearning

rTrapAging.name: rTrapAging
rTrapAging.description: Time in sec. until we erase a trap entry

pTrapAddrTable.description: Table of managers to which traps must be sent. Up to 10 entries in table

pTrapAddrType.name: pTrapAddrType
pTrapAddrType.description: Type of event that should be reported to this address, bit 0 - authentication trap bit 1 - other SNMP traps bit 2 - Error Traps bit 3 - Diagnostic Traps bit 4 - Debug Traps bit 5 - all Enterprise Traps other than fmDiagGenericTrap

pTrapLearning.name: pTrapLearning
pTrapLearning.description: Learn the addresses of the managers automatically.

fmSystemSelfTestLevel.name: fmSystemSelfTestLevel
fmSystemSelfTestLevel.description: Type of self test to be executed upon cold-reset

fmSystemVersion.name: fmSystemVersion
fmSystemVersion.description: Version of the station. The version includes station type, hardware version and software version. The string can include CR and LF

fmSystemFileServer.name: fmSystemFileServer

fmSystemBootFile.name: fmSystemBootFile
fmSystemBootFile.description: Path and file name that is sent as a TFTP request

fmSystemDownLoad.name: fmSystemDownLoad
fmSystemDownLoad.description: Downloading the ESM. When reading the instance of this object the value has no meaning.

fmSystemSlipIpAddr.name: fmSystemSlipIpAddr
fmSystemSlipIpAddr.description: SLIP IP address. This is object is available only when slip interface exist

fmSystemSlipIPNetMask.name: fmSystemSlipIPNetMask
fmSystemSlipIPNetMask.description: SLIP IP Network Mask This is object is available only when slip interface exist

fmSystemSlipBaudRate.name: fmSystemSlipBaudRate
fmSystemSlipBaudRate.description: SLIP Baud rate This is object is available only when slip interface exist

fmSystemSlipParity.name: fmSystemSlipParity

fmSystemSlipStopBits.name: fmSystemSlipStopBits

pfmSystemFileServer.description: IP address to which a TFTP for boot is sent.

pfmSystemBootFile.name: pfmSystemBootFile
pfmSystemBootFile.description: Path and file name that is sent as a TFTP request

pfmSystemReadCommunity.name: pfmSystemReadCommunity
pfmSystemReadCommunity.description: Community string for reading When reading the instance of this object the value has no meaning.

pfmSystemWriteCommunity.name: pfmSystemWriteCommunity
pfmSystemWriteCommunity.description: Community string for writing When reading the instance of this object the value has no meaning.

pfmSystemSlipIpAddr.name: pfmSystemSlipIpAddr
pfmSystemSlipIpAddr.description: SLIP IP address This is object is available only when slip interface exist

pfmSystemSlipIPNetMask.name: pfmSystemSlipIPNetMask
pfmSystemSlipIPNetMask.description: SLIP IP Network Mask This is object is available only when slip interface exist

pfmSystemSlipBaudRate.name: pfmSystemSlipBaudRate
pfmSystemSlipBaudRate.description: SLIP Baud rate This is object is available only when slip interface exist

pfmSystemSlipParity.name: pfmSystemSlipParity
pfmSystemSlipParity.description: SLIP Parity This is object is available only when slip interface exist

pfmSystemSlipStopBits.name: pfmSystemSlipStopBits
pfmSystemSlipStopBits.description: SLIP Stop Bits This is object is available only when slip interface exist

fmSlotMasterClear.name: fmSlotMasterClear
fmSlotMasterClear.description: Upon writing, performs a master clear command on all the slots. When reading the instance of this object the value has no meaning.

fmSlotID.name: fmSlotID
fmSlotID.description: ID of the card in the slot. Special , not-exist, ID identifies a GigaHUB slot that doesn't exist: slot 5, if a HALF MultiHUB installed, or slot 9, if a FULL MultiHUB installed.

fmSlotDescr.name: fmSlotDescr
fmSlotDescr.description: Ascii string. Description of the card

fmSlotInfo.name: fmSlotInfo
fmSlotInfo.description: User general info for the slot. Can be the use of that slot, its location etc...

fmSlotStatus.name: fmSlotStatus
fmSlotStatus.description: Status bits of the card in the slot, organized by card channel. Each channel's status occupies 2 bytes. For more information about the meaning of the status, read the specific user manual of each card.

fmSlotPrevStatus.name: fmSlotPrevStatus
fmSlotPrevStatus.description: Previous status bits of the card in the slot, organized by card channel. Each channel's status occupies 2 bytes. For more information about the meaning of the status, read the specific user manual of each card. This object id is used mainly for traps (see Card Trap).

fmSlotRLBSet.name: fmSlotRLBSet
fmSlotRLBSet.description: Argument: 1 - 4. Perform a RLB set operation on the channel passed as argument. When reading the instance of this object the value has no meaning.

fmSlotRLBClear.name: fmSlotRLBClear
fmSlotRLBClear.description: Argument: 1 - 4. Perform a RLB clear operation on the channel passed as argument. When reading the instance of this object the value has no meaning.

fmSlotTrapMask.name: fmSlotTrapMask
fmSlotTrapMask.description: When the value is 1, no more traps from that slot are sent, until next reset. (temporary mask)

pfmSlotTrapMask.name: pfmSlotTrapMask
pfmSlotTrapMask.description: When the value is 1, no more traps for that slot will be sent, starting after next reset (permanent mask)

fmSlotIpAddr.name: fmSlotIpAddr
fmSlotIpAddr.description: IP address of a channel card.

fmSlotMngAccess.name: fmSlotMngAccess
fmSlotMngAccess.description: This run-time object determines through which interface the SNMP management will be permitted. The default is through the managment bus, via the ESM. This object value is reinitialized to its permanent value after system reset. Setting the object is permitted only for slots containing active SNMP managers. Such cards will change management access immediately according to the specified value. Set values must be either Management-Bus or LAN and the target slot must contain an active SNMP agent.

pfmSlotMngAccess.name: pfmSlotMngAccess
pfmSlotMngAccess.description: This permanent object determines through which interface the SNMP management will be permitted. The default is through the managment bus, via the ESM. This object has no effect on slots not containing SNMP agents. The run-time object will receive this value after system reset only if the value is permitted. Setting the object is permitted only for slots containing active SNMP managers. Such cards will change management access only the next time the card is initialized. Set values must be either Management-Bus or LAN and the target slot must contain an active SNMP agent.

fmSlotEntityIndex.name: fmSlotEntityIndex
fmSlotEntityIndex.description: This object determines the Entity index which the card is a memeber in.

fmSlotCommunity.name: fmSlotCommunity
fmSlotCommunity.description: This object determines the Entity Community which the card is a memeber in.

fmSlotEntityManager.name: fmSlotEntityManager
fmSlotEntityManager.description: This object determines if the card is an SNMP-manageable Entity Manager.

fmLUDescr.name: fmLUDescr
fmLUDescr.description: Ascii string. Description of the logic unit

fmLULoopBackSet.name: fmLULoopBackSet
fmLULoopBackSet.description: Upon writing, performs LLB command. When reading the instance of this object the value has no meaning.

fmLULoopBackClr.name: fmLULoopBackClr
fmLULoopBackClr.description: Upon writing, clear LLB command. When reading the instance of this object the value has no meaning.

fmLUTrapMask.name: fmLUTrapMask
fmLUTrapMask.description: When the value is 1, no more traps from the LU are sent, until next reset. (temporary mask)

pfmLUTrapMask.name: pfmLUTrapMask
pfmLUTrapMask.description: When the value is 1, no more traps for the LU will be sent, starting after next reset (permanent mask)

fmDiagConfig.name: fmDiagConfig
fmDiagConfig.description: Version of the station. The version includes station type, hardware version and software version. The string can include CR and LF

fmDiagTrapInfo.name: fmDiagTrapInfo
fmDiagTrapInfo.description: Used for generic traps. The first word is the trap code. The rest of the string is the extra information. Contains CR and LF char.

fmDiagFaultTable.name: fmDiagFaultTable
fmDiagFaultTable.description: Table of fault reports from the agent

fmDiagFaultIndex.name: fmDiagFaultIndex
fmDiagFaultIndex.description: The fault index in the fault table

fmDiagFaultReport.name: fmDiagFaultReport
fmDiagFaultReport.description: Get the faults detected by the agent

fmDiagDebug.name: fmDiagDebug
fmDiagDebug.description: This object is for factory use only. Users must not write into this variable or improper operation can occur.

fmLUOutOfSync.name: fmLUOutOfSync
fmLUOutOfSync.description: Issued when the Logic unit goes out of synchronization

fmLUReturnToSync.name: fmLUReturnToSync
fmLUReturnToSync.description: Issues as soon as the logic unit returns to synchronization

fmLUPassToMain.name: fmLUPassToMain
fmLUPassToMain.description: Issues as soon as the logic unit pass to main link

fmLUPassToSecond.name: fmLUPassToSecond
fmLUPassToSecond.description: Issues as soon as the logic unit pass to second link

fmLUPrimaryLinkFail.name: fmLUPrimaryLinkFail
fmLUPrimaryLinkFail.description: When primary link of the logic unit fails this trap is issued

fmLUPrimaryLinkOK.name: fmLUPrimaryLinkOK
fmLUPrimaryLinkOK.description: When primary link of the logic unit fails this trap is issued

fmLUSecondLinkFail.name: fmLUSecondLinkFail
fmLUSecondLinkFail.description: When second link of the logic unit fails this trap is issued

fmLUSecondLinkOK.name: fmLUSecondLinkOK
fmLUSecondLinkOK.description: When second link of the logic unit fails this trap is issued

fmLULLBOn.name: fmLULLBOn
fmLULLBOn.description: When the logic unit enters LLB mode

fmLULLBOff.name: fmLULLBOff
fmLULLBOff.description: When the logic unit exits LLB mode

fmLUChangeConfig.name: fmLUChangeConfig
fmLUChangeConfig.description: Issues when a change in the LU configuration is done

fmSlotTrap.name: fmSlotTrap
fmSlotTrap.description: Generated when a significant status has changed in a slot. By xoring the 2 statuses, the NMS can identify the cause of the trap.

fmSlotChangeConfig.name: fmSlotChangeConfig
fmSlotChangeConfig.description: Issued when the system detects changes in its slots configuration

gigaPhyResourceTable.name: gigaPhyResourceTable
gigaPhyResourceTable.description: This table maps resources to backplane segments/ring numbers

gigaPhyResourceEntry.name: gigaPhyResourceEntry
gigaPhyResourceEntry.description: This table maps resources to backplane segments/ring numbers

gigaPhyResLocationType.name: gigaPhyResLocationType
gigaPhyResLocationType.description: A unique integer representing the location type index

gigaPhyResLocation.name: gigaPhyResLocation
gigaPhyResLocation.description: A unique integer representing the location type instance

gigaPhyResIndex.name: gigaPhyResIndex
gigaPhyResIndex.description: A unique integer representing the resource instance at this location

gigaPhyResCapability.name: gigaPhyResCapability
gigaPhyResCapability.description: A unique integer representing the resource capability for attachment to the serial busses.

gigaPhyResSegRing.name: gigaPhyResSegRing
gigaPhyResSegRing.description: A unique integer representing the ring or segment number in which the resource is attached to.

gigaEbmTable.name: gigaEbmTable
gigaEbmTable.description: A list of EBM cards entries, one for each EBM card in the chassis.

gigaEbmIndex.name: gigaEbmIndex
gigaEbmIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a EBM card

gigaEbmDescr.name: gigaEbmDescr
gigaEbmDescr.description: A textual description of the EBM card.

gigaEbmOperStatus.name: gigaEbmOperStatus
gigaEbmOperStatus.description: Actual status of the EBM card: - unknown(1) - don't have the information - empty(2) - no EBM card installed in slot - bad(3) - unable to work due to failure - good(4) - the card is good - active(5) - the card is good and active

chasType.name: chasType
chasType.description: An authoritative identification of the type of hub-based or standalone chassis. By convention this value is allocated within the SMI enterprises subtree(1.3.6.1.4.1), and provides an easy and unambiguous means for determining `what kind of box' is being managed. If this information is not present or unknown, its value should be set to the value: chasTypeUnknown.

chasPhysicalChanges.name: chasPhysicalChanges
chasPhysicalChanges.description: The number of physical changes that have occurred in the chassis since the agent was warm/cold started. This includes additions and removal of modules and entities. Other uses are implementation specific.

chasChassisSerialNumber.name: chasChassisSerialNumber
chasChassisSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the chassis. If no serial number is available then this object should be the zero length string.

chasMultiConf.name: chasMultiConf
chasMultiConf.description: Which type of MultiHUB is installed in the chassis.

chasPhyLocationTable.name: chasPhyLocationTable
chasPhyLocationTable.description: This table summarises the different classes of and types of modular physical locations in the chassis. This includes but is not limited to slot within a chassis, power supply bay.

chasPhyLocationTypeIndex.name: chasPhyLocationTypeIndex
chasPhyLocationTypeIndex.description: This uniquely identifies the physical location type within the chassis.

chasPhyLocationCount.name: chasPhyLocationCount
chasPhyLocationCount.description: This defines the number of physical locations of this type exist within the chassis.

chasPhyLocationType.name: chasPhyLocationType
chasPhyLocationType.description: Uniquely identifies the 'type' of the physical location within the chassis.

chasPhyLocationDescr.name: chasPhyLocationDescr
chasPhyLocationDescr.description: Each type of physical location within the chassis is given a textual name.

chasPhyModuleTable.name: chasPhyModuleTable
chasPhyModuleTable.description: This table defines the physical modules within a chassis. This is done by defining the type physical modules and the physical location where it resides. This table also provides a mapping between physical modules and their location within the chassis.

chasPhyModuleEntry.name: chasPhyModuleEntry
chasPhyModuleEntry.description: An entry in this table that describes a physical module that resides at a given physcial location within the chassis.

chasPhyModuleLocationType.name: chasPhyModuleLocationType
chasPhyModuleLocationType.description: An instance of a module is identified by the physical location in which it resides. The physical location is identified by location type index and location index (instance of that location type). This object defines an instance of the chasPhyLocationType.

chasPhyModuleLocation.name: chasPhyModuleLocation
chasPhyModuleLocation.description: An instance of a module is identified by the physical location which it resides. The physical location is identified by location type index and location index (instance of that location type). This object defines the instance of a particular location type. It must be within the bounds defined by chasPhyLocationCount.

chasPhyModuleType.name: chasPhyModuleType
chasPhyModuleType.description: An authoritative identification of the type of physcial module in this physical location. A value of chasModuleUnknown indicates that the type of physical module is unknown.

chasPhyModuleSwVersion.name: chasPhyModuleSwVersion
chasPhyModuleSwVersion.description: A textual description of the version/revision level for this module's software. If not realized this value should be set to the zero-length string.

chasPhyModuleHwVersion.name: chasPhyModuleHwVersion
chasPhyModuleHwVersion.description: A textual description of the version/revision level for this module's firmware. If not realized this value should be set to the zero-length string.

chasPhyModuleSerialNumber.name: chasPhyModuleSerialNumber
chasPhyModuleSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the physical module present in this physical location. If the physical location table is implemented as dense and the slot is empty this value will be the zero length string. If no serial number is available for a physical module this value should set to a zero length string.

chasPhyModuleDescription.name: chasPhyModuleDescription
chasPhyModuleDescription.description: A textual description of the physical module plugged that resides in this physical location. If not available this value should be set to a zero length string.

chasPhyModuleLastChangeTime.name: chasPhyModuleLastChangeTime
chasPhyModuleLastChangeTime.description: The value of MIB-II's sysUpTime (in the agent supporting this chassis MIB) at which a module was last inserted or initialized. If the module has not changed since the last network managment system reinitialized then this object has a zero value.

chasPhyModuleAdminStatus.name: chasPhyModuleAdminStatus
chasPhyModuleAdminStatus.description: Provides desired state of the given physical module. Notice that not all values may be supported by the specified physical module. In this case and SNMP error will be returned when the set is attempted. A physical module maybe activated by writing a value of enable(2). A physical module may be de-activated by writing a value of disable(3). In a disabled state a physical module is present in the chassis but is benign. Writing a value of sw-reset(4) initiates a software reset sequence. Writing a value of hw-reset(7) initiates a hardware reset sequence. A value of programLoad(5) initiates a software load sequence. Writing a value of test(6) should start a self test sequence within the physical module.

chasPhyModuleOperStatus.name: chasPhyModuleOperStatus
chasPhyModuleOperStatus.description: Provides operational status of the module. The following are possible definitions of the values. The exact definition of the values is implementation specific. A value of other(1) implies some undetermined state, possibly as a result of setting phyAdminStatus to a value of disable(3). A value of invalid(2) could have the possible meaning that the module exists but the chassis manager has no direct control over the module. A value of testing(3) may be a diagnostic state. A value of operational(4) implies that the entity is running with no errors or warnings. State resetInProgress(5) implies equivalent of setting phyAdminStatus to reset(4). The states of warning(6), nonFatalError(7), fatalError(8) reflect conditions detected during operation. The entity may or may not be still functional. For example if a modules value of phyAdminStatus is disable(3) and is set to enable(2) then phyOperStatus may enter a state of testing(3) then change to a value of operational(4).

chasEntityTable.name: chasEntityTable
chasEntityTable.description: A table that contains information about the 'logical' networking devices (entities) in this chassis.

chasEntityEntry.name: chasEntityEntry
chasEntityEntry.description: Information concerning an entity in the chassis. Conceptual rows may not be created or deleted with SNMP operations.

chasEntityIndex.name: chasEntityIndex
chasEntityIndex.description: A unique index for the entity for which this entry contains information.

chasEntityObjectID.name: chasEntityObjectID
chasEntityObjectID.description: The specific type of entity. The value of this object is analagous to MIB-II's sysObjectId. In particular, it has the same value as would be returned if the SNMP Party (identified by chasEntityParty) and/or the community (identified by chasIpAddress and chasCommunity), were queried for sysObjectId.

chasEntityDescr.name: chasEntityDescr
chasEntityDescr.description: A textual description of the entity. The value of this object is analagous to MIB-II's sysDescr. In particular, it has the same value as would be returned if the SNMP Party (identified by chasEntityParty) and/or the community (identified by chasIpAddress and chasCommunity), were queried for sysDescr.

chasEntityAdminStatus.name: chasEntityAdminStatus
chasEntityAdminStatus.description: Provides the administratively desired state of the given entity. An entity is activated by writing a value of enable(2). An entity may be de-activated by writing a value of disable(3). In a disabled state, a entity does exist within the given chassis, but is benign. A disabled entity is available for subsequent activation. Writing a value of reset(4) specifies an entity should initiate a reset sequence. Writing a value of programload(5) specifies an entity should initiate a program load sequence. Writing a value of test(6) specifies an entity should initiate a testing sequence. Agent support of the writing of any of the values of this object is implementation-specific. For example, this object might be read only for entities that disabling would compromise the integrity of the chassis.

chasEntityOperStatus.name: chasEntityOperStatus
chasEntityOperStatus.description: Provides operational status of the entity. The following are possible definitions of the values. The exact definition of the values is implementation specific. A value of other(1) implies some undetermined state, possibly as a result of setting chasEntityAdminStatus to a value of disable(3). A value of invalid(2) could have the possible meaning that the entity exists but the chassis manager has no direct control of the entity. A value of testing(3) may be a diagnostic state. A value of operational(4) implies that the entity is running with no errors or warnings. State resetInProgress(5) implies equivalent of setting chasEntityAdminStatus to reset(4). The states of warning(6), nonFatalError(7), fatalError(8) reflect conditions detected during operation. The entity may or may not be still functional. State loading(10) is a result of asserting programload(5) in chasEntityAdminStatus. For example if an entities value of chasEntityAdminStatus is disable(3) and is set to enable(2) then chasEntityOperStatus may enter a state of testing(3) then change to a value of operational(4).

chasEntityTimeStamp.name: chasEntityTimeStamp
chasEntityTimeStamp.description: The value of MIB-II's sysUpTime (in the agent supporting this MIB) at which this entity was last (re-)initialized. If the entity has not been initialized then this object has a zero value.

chasEntityParty.name: chasEntityParty
chasEntityParty.description: The SNMP Party which provides access to the detailed management information for this entity. Note that the definition of a SNMP Party includes the location at which it executes, the authentication and privacy algorithms and parameters required to access the management entity. In order for a SNMP manager to be able to access the Party, that manager must have prior knowledge of the Party. A party is named by a 'Party'. For a entity which is not managed through access to a SNMP Party, the value of this object is 0.0

chasEntityContext.name: chasEntityContext
chasEntityContext.description: The SNMPv2 Context indentifier the chasEntityContext in conjunction with chasEntityParty defines access to the MIB view for this entity.

chasEntityCommunity.name: chasEntityCommunity
chasEntityCommunity.description: The SNMP Community which executes at the address chasEntityIpAddress, and provides access to the detailed management information for this entity. For a entity which is not managed through access to a SNMP Community, the value of this object is the zero-length string.

chasEntityIpAddress.name: chasEntityIpAddress
chasEntityIpAddress.description: The address of the SNMP agent which responds to messages for the SNMP Community identified by chasEntityCommunity. When access is via proxy, this variable contains the address of the proxy agent. For a entity which is not managed through access to a SNMP Community, the value of this object is 0.0.0.0.

chasPhyResourceTable.name: chasPhyResourceTable
chasPhyResourceTable.description: This table defines a physical relationship between physical modules and resources. A resource is a building block. A resource defines the type of relationship between entities. This may be a back plane connection between physical modules sharing the same entity. It may be a network segment that connects multiple entities. This table then defines the physical mapping of resources and physical modules onto entities.

chasPhyResourceEntry.name: chasPhyResourceEntry
chasPhyResourceEntry.description: Defines a particular physical configuration relationship.

chasPhyResLocationType.name: chasPhyResLocationType
chasPhyResLocationType.description: A resource exists on a particular module. A module is identified by it's physical location. Physical location is defined by location type and an instance of that physical location type. This object defines the location type. This object can be used in conjunction with chasPhyResLocation to index the module table.

chasPhyResLocation.name: chasPhyResLocation
chasPhyResLocation.description: A resource exists on a particular module. A module is identified by it's physical location. Physical location is defined by location type and an instance of that physical location type. This object defines a particular instance of the physical location.

chasPhyResIndex.name: chasPhyResIndex
chasPhyResIndex.description: A unique index for the chassis resource on this particular physical module.

chasPhyResAssignment.name: chasPhyResAssignment
chasPhyResAssignment.description: The physical module resource is assigned to a specific entity. This object defines the entity to which this resource is currently assigned. Notice, not all implementations may support this object as read-write. If read-write is supported assignment may still fail due to a number of reasons such as insufficient resources, invalid configuration.

chasPhyResEntitySubIndex.name: chasPhyResEntitySubIndex
chasPhyResEntitySubIndex.description: Provides a unique index that can be used to identify the relationship in terms of the entity.

chasLogResourceTable.name: chasLogResourceTable
chasLogResourceTable.description: Defines a logical configuration relationship which is a relationship between entities and resources and the physical module that the relationship exists on.

chasLogResEntity.name: chasLogResEntity
chasLogResEntity.description: The entity ID for which this logical configuration relationship exists.

chasLogResEntitySubIndex.name: chasLogResEntitySubIndex
chasLogResEntitySubIndex.description: The entity sub index for which this logical configuration relationship exists. The logical relationship is identified by a resource assignment to an entity. The sub index defines a particular instance of the mapping of physical configuration onto an entity.

chasLogResLocationType.name: chasLogResLocationType
chasLogResLocationType.description: A module is defined by it's physical location type and an instance of that physical location. This object defines the physical location type portion of the physical module identifier that this logical configuration exists for.

chasLogResLocation.name: chasLogResLocation
chasLogResLocation.description: A module is defined by it's physical location type and an instance of that physical location. This object defines the instance physical location (location index) portion of the physical module identifier that this logical configuration exists for.

chasLogResIndex.name: chasLogResIndex
chasLogResIndex.description: The value of this object refers to a particular instance of a resource, as defined by chasResourceIndex, for which this relationship is defined. This together with chasLogResLocationType and chasLogResLocation completes the mapping of the logical configuration on to the physical module and resource combination.

chasPowerSupplyTable.name: chasPowerSupplyTable
chasPowerSupplyTable.description: A list of power supply entries, one for each power supply in the chassis.

chasPowerSupplyIndex.name: chasPowerSupplyIndex
chasPowerSupplyIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a power supply. This may correspond to a hardware power supply slot, which may or may not be the same as a network device slot (chasSlotIndex).

chasPowerSupplyDescr.name: chasPowerSupplyDescr
chasPowerSupplyDescr.description: A textual description of the power supply, including the vendor's name and version.

chasPowerSupplyAdminStatus.name: chasPowerSupplyAdminStatus
chasPowerSupplyAdminStatus.description: Desired status of the power supply.

chasPowerSupplyOperStatus.name: chasPowerSupplyOperStatus
chasPowerSupplyOperStatus.description: Actual status of the power supply: - unknown(1) - status not known. - empty(2) - no power supply installed in slot - disabled(3) - unable to supply power due to chasPowerSupplyAdminStatus - bad(4) - unable to supply power due to failure - warning(5) - supplying power but an output or sensor is bad or warning - standby(6) - believed usable but not supplying power - engaged(7) - supplying power - redundant(8) - supplying power but not needed It is an implementation specific matter whether the agent keeps entries with status unknown(1) or empty(2) in the table.

chasPowerSupplyHealthText.name: chasPowerSupplyHealthText
chasPowerSupplyHealthText.description: A textual description of the power supply's operational status. Agents may use this string to provide detailed information on current failures, including how they were detected, and/or instructions for problem resolution. The contents are agent-specific.

chasPowerSupplyWarnings.name: chasPowerSupplyWarnings
chasPowerSupplyWarnings.description: The number of times chasPowerSupplyOperStatus has gone to warning(5).

chasPowerSupplyFailures.name: chasPowerSupplyFailures
chasPowerSupplyFailures.description: The number of times chasPowerSupplyOperStatus has gone to bad(4).

chasPowerSupplyLocationType.name: chasPowerSupplyLocationType
chasPowerSupplyLocationType.description: This defines the instance of a physical location type of the power supply. Location Type together with location index completely defines the location of a power supply.

chasPowerSupplyLocationIndex.name: chasPowerSupplyLocationIndex
chasPowerSupplyLocationIndex.description: Defines a particular instance of a physical location type.

chasPowerSupplyOutputTable.name: chasPowerSupplyOutputTable
chasPowerSupplyOutputTable.description: A list of power supply output entries, one for each output of each power supply in the chassis.

chasPowerSupplyOutputEntry.name: chasPowerSupplyOutputEntry
chasPowerSupplyOutputEntry.description: Values for a power supply output.

chasPowerSupplyIdIndex.name: chasPowerSupplyIdIndex
chasPowerSupplyIdIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a power supply. This may correspond to a hardware power supply slot, which may or may not be the same as a network device slot (chasSlotIndex).

chasPowerSupplyOutputIndex.name: chasPowerSupplyOutputIndex
chasPowerSupplyOutputIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an output for the power supply.

chasPowerSupplyOutputStatus.name: chasPowerSupplyOutputStatus
chasPowerSupplyOutputStatus.description: Actual status of the power supply: - unknown(1) status not known - bad(2) unable to supply power due to failure - warning(3) supplying power but marginally - good(4) supplying power It is an implementation specific matter whether the agent keeps entries with status unknown(1) in the table. If unknown(1), offered values and counters are meaningless.

chasPowerSupplyOutputNominalVoltage.name: chasPowerSupplyOutputNominalVoltage
chasPowerSupplyOutputNominalVoltage.description: In hundredths of a volt, the voltage the output is supposed to supply, such as -5, +5, +12, -15, etc.

chasPowerSupplyOutputOfferedVoltage.name: chasPowerSupplyOutputOfferedVoltage
chasPowerSupplyOutputOfferedVoltage.description: In hundredths of a volt, the voltage actually offered by the output. If chasPowerSupplyOutputStatus is good(4), the value 0 means offered voltage is not available.

chasPowerSupplyOutputOfferedWattage.name: chasPowerSupplyOutputOfferedWattage
chasPowerSupplyOutputOfferedWattage.description: In hundredths of a watt, the wattage actually offered by the output. If chasPowerSupplyOutputStatus is good(4), the value 0 means offered wattage is not available.

chasPowerSupplyOutputWarnings.name: chasPowerSupplyOutputWarnings
chasPowerSupplyOutputWarnings.description: The number of times chasPowerSupplyOutputStatus has gone to warning(3).

chasPowerSupplyOutputFailures.name: chasPowerSupplyOutputFailures
chasPowerSupplyOutputFailures.description: The number of times chasPowerSupplyOutputStatus has gone to bad(2).

chasEnvironTable.name: chasEnvironTable
chasEnvironTable.description: A list of environmental entries, one for each environmental sensor in the chassis.

chasEnvironSensor.name: chasEnvironSensor
chasEnvironSensor.description: The identification of an environmental sensor. Other AutonomousType values may be defined elsewhere, in association with specific protocols. However, this document assigns those of known interest as of this writing.

chasEnvironStatus.name: chasEnvironStatus
chasEnvironStatus.description: Actual status indicated by the sensor. It is an implementation specific matter whether the agent keeps entries with status unknown(1) in the table. If unknown(1), counters are meaningless.

chasEnvironWarnings.name: chasEnvironWarnings
chasEnvironWarnings.description: The number of times chasEnvironStatus has gone to warning(3).

chasEnvironFailures.name: chasEnvironFailures
chasEnvironFailures.description: The number of times chasEnvironStatus has gone to bad(2).

chasEnvironLocationType.name: chasEnvironLocationType
chasEnvironLocationType.description: Defines the actual type of physical location that this environmental sensor occupies.

chasEnvironLocationIndex.name: chasEnvironLocationIndex
chasEnvironLocationIndex.description: This defines the particular instance of a physical location type which this environmental sensor occupies.

chasEnvironIndex.name: chasEnvironIndex
chasEnvironIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an environmental sensor.

gigaPowerSupplyTrap.name: gigaPowerSupplyTrap
gigaPowerSupplyTrap.description: This trap message is generated as soon as one of the power supply has changed its operational status.

gigaSensorTrap.name: gigaSensorTrap
gigaSensorTrap.description: This trap message is generated when there is a change in enviromental sensor status.

gigaHostAuthTrap.name: gigaHostAuthTrap
gigaHostAuthTrap.description: This trap is generated when an unauthorized host attempts to perform an SNMP SET operation.

gigaModuleTrap.name: gigaModuleTrap
gigaModuleTrap.description: This trap message is generated when there is a change in module operational status

gigaModuleEmptyTrap.name: gigaModuleEmptyTrap
gigaModuleEmptyTrap.description: This trap is generated when a module is removed from a modular slot.

gigaModuleNotEmptyTrap.name: gigaModuleNotEmptyTrap
gigaModuleNotEmptyTrap.description: This trap is generated when a module is inserted in a modular slot.

gigaPhyResAttachChangeTrap.name: gigaPhyResAttachChangeTrap
gigaPhyResAttachChangeTrap.description: This trap is generated when physical module resource is changed it's segment/ring attachment.

gigaPhyResConfigChangeTrap.name: gigaPhyResConfigChangeTrap
gigaPhyResConfigChangeTrap.description: This trap is generated when there is a global change in physical module resources configuration.

gigaEbmTrap.name: gigaEbmTrap
gigaEbmTrap.description: This trap message is generated as soon as one of the EBM cards has changed its operational status.

fmSlotIPAddressChange.name: fmSlotIPAddressChange
fmSlotIPAddressChange.description: This trap is generated when IP Address is changed in a slot.
